{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1101: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. If $u=\\{u_1<u_2<\\cdots\\}$ is a sequence of integers such that $(u_i,u_j)=1$ for all $i\\neq j$ and $\\sum \\frac{1}{u_i}<\\infty$ then let $\\{a_1<a_2<\\cdots\\}$ be the sequence of integers which are not divisible by any of the $u_i$. For any $x$ define $t_x$ by\\[u_1\\cdots u_{t_x}\\leq x< u_1\\cdots u_{t_x}u_{t_x+1}.\\]We call such a sequence $u_i$ good if, for all $\\epsilon>0$, if $x$ is sufficiently large then\\[\\max_{a_k<x} (a_{k+1}-a_k) < (1+\\epsilon)t_x \\prod_{i}\\left(1-\\frac{1}{u_i}\\right)^{-1}.\\]Is there a good sequence such that $u_n< n^{O(1)}$? Is there a good sequence such that $u_n\\leq e^{o(n)}$? Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_06e459a0ec28fb7c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1101.erdos_1101.parts.ii https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1101.erdos_1101.parts.ii.","id":"vf_28b56e7e5384e2f1","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Candidate partial result (solution to second part).","id":"vf_9aaf6fe64a207cd2","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1101.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_06e459a0ec28fb7c","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:1101","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_28b56e7e5384e2f1","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:1101","trust":"s